abstract: The SLEDAI 2000 (SLEDAI-2K) Responder Index 50 (SRI-50) is a novel index that measures â‰¥ 50% in each of the 24 descriptors of SLEDAI-2K and generates a total score reflecting disease activity overall. The SLE Responder Index (SRI) has been successfully used to identify responders in recent trials. This is the first study to evaluate the ability of SRI-50 to identify responders, defined as patients who had a clinically important improvement over their baseline value over 12 months. We compared the performance of SRI-50 with that of SLEDAI-2K and SRI at 6 and 12 months in identifying responders.
